                <h1>Understanding the Declaration of Independence</h1>
                <p>The Declaration of Independence, adopted on July 4, 1776, marked the American colonies' assertion of autonomy from British rule. This pivotal document, primarily authored by Thomas Jefferson, articulates the fundamental principles of liberty and the rights of individuals. It remains a symbol of democracy and a benchmark for freedom worldwide.</p>
